prompt: If Glimberish(x,y) and Zindlequack(y,z) then what are the possible relationships between x and z?
answer:
Given  
  • Glimberish(x,y) ≡ x TPP y  
  • Zindlequack(y,z) ≡ y TPP⁻¹ z (i.e. z NTPP y)  
the standard RCC‑8 composition TPP ◦ NTPP⁻¹ yields exactly five possible base‐relations between x and z:

  1. Blorpticate(x,z)  
  2. Snarfloon(x,z)  
  3. Twizzlump(x,z)  
  4. Narpulate(x,z)  
  5. Zindlequack(x,z)

### Answer: Blorpticate(x,z), Snarfloon(x,z), Twizzlump(x,z), Narpulate(x,z), Zindlequack(x,z)
